verbose_text: Targeting these pathways has shown some promise--cabozantinib (XL-184) inhibits tyrosine kinases of c-Met and VEGF, and in phase II clinical trial, demonstrated significant benefit specifically for CRPC patients with bone metastases; However, it did not reach its primary endpoint (bone pain alleviation) in phase III trial, with no significant difference in bone pain alleviation between the treatment and control (mitoxantrone / prednisone) arms.
